  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single variation axis of a variable font, including its tag, value range, default value, and visibility.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` describes one axis of a variable font, including its
four-character OpenType tag, the allowed range of values, the default value,
and whether the axis is hidden from end-user interfaces.

Retrieve the axes for a typeface using
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters> or
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.GetVariationDesignParameters*>.

This struct is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var axes = typeface.VariationDesignParameters;
foreach (var axis in axes)
{
    Console.WriteLine(
        $"{axis.Tag}: min={axis.Min}, max={axis.Max}, default={axis.Default}, hidden={axis.IsHidden}");
}
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
